  <slide>
    <title>Why was the World Wide Web Invented?</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>Tim Berners Lee was a scientist at CERN particle accelerator lab.</li>
        <li>Scientists were having problems sharing and collaborating on documents and research results, for example some of the word processing tools available in the late 1980's:
          <ul>
            <li>WordStar</li>
            <li>WordPerfect</li>
            <li>Microsoft Word</li>
            <li>Apple Write</li>
            <li>LaTex</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
        <li>Tim had an idea to not only share information between people, but with everyone.</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

  <slide>
    <title>Purpose of the World Wide Web</title>
    <contents>
      <ul>
        <li>Sharing scientific information.</li>
        <li>Common platform for viewing, creating, editing and linking online information.</li>
        <li>Open standards for everyone to use.</li>
      </ul>
    </contents>
  </slide>

